{#-
  Rendered by datus into the agent's system prompt with StrictUndefined,
  trim_blocks and lstrip_blocks. Context: plugin_name, profiles, config_path,
  config_mutable (False in managed API deployments — never point at the setup
  skill there).

  `profiles` carries ONLY fields declared non-secret in the manifest's
  config_schema (api_base_url, username, dags_folder, ...). token / password
  and the s3 credential leaves (s3.secret_access_key, s3.session_token) are
  stripped structurally BEFORE rendering and must never be referenced here;
  the stripping recurses into the declared s3 object, so undeclared s3 keys
  are dropped too. Use cfg.get("field") for optional fields so missing keys
  never trip StrictUndefined. Because `token` is stripped, the auth label is
  derived from `username` presence alone: username -> username/password,
  otherwise token.
-#}
{% if profiles %}
## Airflow
Operate remote Apache Airflow 3.x deployments through `datus airflow <group> <subcommand>` (REST API backed; supports `--profile <env>` before the group).
Groups: `dags` (list, details, list-runs, trigger [--wait], pause/unpause, state, clear-run, delete, show, source, next-execution, list-import-errors, and `deploy` to ship DAG files to S3 or a dags folder), `tasks` (list, state, states-for-dag-run, clear, failed-deps, logs), `variables`, `connections`, `pools` (each with list/get/set-or-add/delete/import/export), `assets` (list, details, materialize, events), `backfill` (create/list/pause/unpause/cancel), `providers list`, `plugins`, `config`, `jobs check`, `version`, `health`.
Add `-o json` for machine-readable output. Consult the `airflow` skill for details before composing non-trivial commands.
